  "prompt": "What if Obama dies before Trump is inaugurated? Would Joe Biden assume presidency or Trump take oath earlier than planned?",
  "response": "If Barack Obama were to pass away before Donald Trump was inaugurated on January 20, 2017, it would not impact the timing of Trump's inauguration. The presidential succession is governed by the U.S. Constitution and laws surrounding it. \n\nIn this scenario, Joe Biden, as the sitting Vice President, would remain in his position until Trump is inaugurated. The inauguration is a set constitutional event that takes place on January 20th following the election. Trump would still take the oath of office at that scheduled time, and Joe Biden would not assume the presidency.\n\nThe death of a sitting president does not alter the election outcomes or the term of the vice president. Therefore, Trump's inauguration would proceed as planned, and he would become the 45th President of the United States at that time.",
